biolockj.module.implicit.parser

Class ParserModuleImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • biolockj.module.BioModuleImpl
      • biolockj.module.ScriptModuleImpl
        • biolockj.module.JavaModuleImpl
          • biolockj.module.implicit.parser.ParserModuleImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BioModule, ParserModule, JavaModule, ScriptModule, Comparable<BioModule>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Humann2Parser, Kraken2Parser, KrakenParser, Metaphlan2Parser, QiimeParser, RdpParser

    public abstract class ParserModuleImpl
extends JavaModuleImpl
implements ParserModule
    Parser BioModules read ClassifierModule output to build standardized OTU count tables. This class provides the default abstract implementation.

      • isValid

        protected boolean isValid(OtuNode node)
                   throws Exception
        Some ClassifierModules can include taxonomy level identifiers without an OTU name in the sample report files. This method verifies the node exists, has a valid sample ID, and that no empty String OTU names are reported.
        Parameters:
        node - OtuNode build from 1 line of a ClassifierModule output file
        Returns:
        boolean if OtuNode is valid
        Throws:
        Exception - if errors occur checking if node is valid
